A. Import training datasets of HANet

creat a dataloader

{% raw %}

class handover_grasping_dataset[source]

handover_grasping_dataset(data_dir, mode='train', color_type='jpg', depth_type='npy') :: Dataset

Dataloader.

This Class is a dataloader for HANet.

Args: data_dir(str) : Path include folders name 'color' and 'depth' and 'depth_npy'. mode(str) : Define this loader is for training or inference. color_type(str) : color image format. depth_type(str) : depth image format.

Returns: A dict

{% endraw %} {% raw %}

class rosenberger_dataloader[source]

rosenberger_dataloader(data_dir, color_type='jpg', depth_type='npy')

Dataloader.

This Class is a dataloader for GGCNN.

Args: data_dir(str) : Path include folders name 'color' and 'depth' and 'depth_npy'. color_type(str) : color image format. depth_type(str) : depth image format.

Returns: A dict

{% endraw %} {% raw %}

class parallel_jaw_based_grasping_dataset[source]

parallel_jaw_based_grasping_dataset(data_dir, use_zeng=True, scale=0.125) :: Dataset

Dataloader.

This Class is a dataloader for ConvNet (Andy Zeng alg).

Args: data_dir(str) : Path include folders name 'color' and 'depth' and 'depth_npy'. use_zeng(bool) : True : load origin parallel_jaw_based_grasping_dataset, False : other datasets

Returns: A dict

Show the training dataset of HANet (3a)

Data num : 1080

Image size : RGB (224x224x3) / Depth (224x224) / Label (224x224x4)

senario: An object held by 1 of 3 sitting people at the desk or a laying person at the patient bed

Source:

  1. RGB-D images taken by the camera arranged at the robot arm
  2. RGB-D images synthesized by the colored point clouds from 2 cameras arranged at the robot arms respectively

This dataset can be split to 3 parts due to different collection environment or ways to generate.

Split:

  1. Data collected in Lab environment by Intel D435 RGB-D camera.
  2. Data collected in medical bed environment by Intel D435 RGB-D camera.
  3. Data generated by height-map (point-cloud).

Load data

{% raw %} 
from torch.utils.data import  DataLoader
from matplotlib import pyplot as plt
import cv2
from handover_grasping.Datavisualizer import handover_grasping_dataset
import numpy as np

# loal data
DATA_PATH = '/home/arg/handover_grasping/data/HANet_training_datasets'

# split_1
dataset_spilt_1 = handover_grasping_dataset(DATA_PATH, color_type='png', mode='train_split_1')
dataloader_spilt_1 = DataLoader(dataset_spilt_1, batch_size = 1, shuffle = True, num_workers = 8)

# # split_2
dataset_spilt_2 = handover_grasping_dataset(DATA_PATH, color_type='png', mode='train_split_2')
dataloader_spilt_2 = DataLoader(dataset_spilt_2, batch_size = 1, shuffle = True, num_workers = 8)

# split_3
dataset_spilt_3 = handover_grasping_dataset(DATA_PATH, color_type='png', mode='train_split_3')
dataloader_spilt_3 = DataLoader(dataset_spilt_3, batch_size = 1, shuffle = True, num_workers = 8)
{% endraw %}

Plot the data (Split_1)

In Lab environment

{% raw %} 
for _ in range(4):
    # Get smaple data
    batch = next(iter(dataloader_spilt_1))
    # RGB and Depth image
    color = batch['color_origin'][0].numpy()
    depth = batch['depth_origin'][0].numpy()

    # object angle id and label
    idx = batch['id'][0].numpy()
    label = batch['label'][0].permute(2,0,1).numpy()[:,:,idx]
    label = cv2.resize(label, (640,480))
    
    # Visualize
    fig = plt.figure(figsize=(10, 10))
    fig.add_subplot(1, 3, 1)
    plt.axis('off')
    plt.title('RGB')
    plt.imshow(color)

    fig.add_subplot(1, 3, 2)
    plt.axis('off')
    plt.title('Depth')
    plt.imshow(depth, cmap='gray')

    fig.add_subplot(1, 3, 3)
    plt.axis('off')
    plt.title('Label')
    plt.imshow(label, cmap='gray')
{% endraw %}

Plot the data (Split_3)

Generate by height-map (point cloud

{% raw %} 
for _ in range(4):
    # Get smaple data
    batch = next(iter(dataloader_spilt_3))
    # RGB and Depth image
    color = batch['color_origin'][0].numpy()
    depth = batch['depth_origin'][0].numpy()

    # object angle id and label
    idx = batch['id'][0].numpy()
    label = batch['label'][0].permute(2,0,1).numpy()[:,:,idx]
    label = cv2.resize(label, (640,480))
    
    # Visualize
    fig = plt.figure(figsize=(10, 10))
    fig.add_subplot(1, 3, 1)
    plt.axis('off')
    plt.title('RGB')
    plt.imshow(color)

    fig.add_subplot(1, 3, 2)
    plt.axis('off')
    plt.title('Depth')
    plt.imshow(depth, cmap='gray')
    
    M = np.float32([[1, 0, -80], [0, 1, 0]])
    label = cv2.warpAffine(label, M, (label.shape[1], label.shape[0]))

    fig.add_subplot(1, 3, 3)
    plt.axis('off')
    plt.title('Label')
    plt.imshow(label, cmap='gray')

B. Import simple testing datasets of HANet

Visualize HANet Easy Testing Datasets (3b)

Data num : 200

Image size : RGB (224x224x3) / Depth (224x224)

senario: An object held by 1 of 3 sitting people at the desk or a laying person at the patient bed

Source:

  1. RGB-D images taken by the camera front of the bed

Load data

{% raw %} 
from handover_grasping.Datavisualizer import rosenberger_dataloader
hanet_easy_loader = rosenberger_dataloader('/home/arg/handover_grasping/data/HANet_easy_datasets')
{% endraw %}

Plot the data

{% raw %} 
for _ in range(4):
    # Get sample data
    batch = hanet_easy_loader.get_next_data(vis_bbox=True)
    color = batch['color']
    color = cv2.cvtColor(color, cv2.COLOR_BGR2RGB)
    color_bbox = batch['color_bbox']
    depth = batch['depth']
    mask_hand = batch['mask_hand']
    mask_body = batch['mask_body']
    bbox = batch['bbox']
    
    # Visualize
    fig = plt.figure(figsize=(20, 20))
    fig.add_subplot(1, 5, 1)
    plt.axis('off')
    plt.title('RGB')
    plt.imshow(color)

    fig.add_subplot(1, 5, 2)
    plt.axis('off')
    plt.title('Depth')
    plt.imshow(depth, cmap='gray')

    fig.add_subplot(1, 5, 3)
    plt.axis('off')
    plt.title('mask_hand')
    plt.imshow(mask_hand)

    fig.add_subplot(1, 5, 4)
    plt.axis('off')
    plt.title('mask_body')
    plt.imshow(mask_body)

    fig.add_subplot(1, 5, 5)
    plt.axis('off')
    plt.title('bbox visualize')
    plt.imshow(color_bbox)
    
    plt.show()
{% endraw %}

D. Import testing datasets of ConvNet

Visualize testing dataset of ConvNet

ref:https://github.com/andyzeng/arc-robot-vision

This dataloader will load image and rotate 16 time from 0 to 337.5 degrees

Load data

{% raw %} 
import cv2
from torch.utils.data import  DataLoader
from matplotlib import pyplot as plt
from handover_grasping.Datavisualizer import parallel_jaw_based_grasping_dataset
from handover_grasping.utils import Image_table

dataset = parallel_jaw_based_grasping_dataset('/home/arg/handover_grasping/data/parallel-jaw-grasping-dataset', use_zeng=True)
dataloader = DataLoader(dataset, batch_size = 1, shuffle = False, num_workers = 1)

batch = next(iter(dataloader))

# RGB and Depth image list, each contain 16 images
colors = batch['color_origin']
depths = batch['depth_origin']

  1. RGB

color_list = []
title_list = []
for i in range(len(colors)):
    color_sub = colors[i][0].numpy()
    color_list.append(color_sub[:,:,[2,1,0]])
    title_list.append('Angle : '+str(i*22.5))
    
Image_table(4, 4, color_list, title_list)
{% endraw %}
  1. Depth
{% raw %} 
depth_list = []
for i in range(len(depths)):
    depth_sub = depths[i][0].numpy()
    depth_list.append(depth_sub)
    
Image_table(4, 4, depth_list, title_list)
